    <div id="ash_4.0">
        <h1>4.0 Group Name Management</h1>
        <p>The "Group Name Management" link is for creating new "groups", and making 
        changes to existing "groups" from a master list. </p>

        <p>Left clicking on "Group Name Management" in the "System Administration" window, 
        will display a list of existing "Groups", "Group Leaders" and options to "show", 
        "edit" or "destroy" each. Left clicking "Show" will display the group name, 
        leader name, and description in a read only format. Left clicking "edit" will 
        allow you to edit this information in an open form. Left clicking "Destroy" will 
        delete the selected group along with all data. The administrator will be asked 
        once if this is a desirable outcome.</p>
        <p><b>Warning: </b>After left clicking "Okay" 
        the data will be deleted and not retrievable. </p>
        <p>Creating a new Group Name: Below the list of Group Names is a "New Group 
        Name" link. Left clicking on this link will display a form for creating a new 
        group name in the Map Viewer. Fill in the information for group name, leader 
        name, and a description of the group. Click the "Create" button. The information 
        you have provided will be displayed in a read only format. </p>
    </div>
